{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"Cross-session corroboration (independent /rebar-debug run, session != e0317d38): I\nreached the SAME confirmed root cause independently — `git commit` in the transition\nwrite path (txn.py:268 via run_git_write) reads HEAD to set the new commit's parent;\nwhen HEAD's commit object is transiently unreadable on a CI runner FS it dies with\nexactly `fatal: could not parse HEAD` (exit 128), while `git add` does not. Same\nrunner-FS transient-loose-object class as edf7 (commit 2271912cc), but on the READ\nside; run_git_write self-heals only index.lock, not this signature. Fix direction\n(centralize a signature-scoped transient retry in gitutil.run_git_write, covering\ntxn/delete/compact + event_append commit) matches — agreed.\n\nOne extra data point: I stress-ran the exact heavy sequence 480× across 12 parallel\nworkers WITH forced aggressive gc (gc.auto=1, autoDetach=true) on macOS and got ZERO\nreproductions — consistent with this being a runner-FS transient (not a background-gc\nref race), and supports the deterministic-injection RED oracle over trying to race it.\n\nDeferring to this session (e0317d38), which is ahead in Phase 2 — NOT pushing a\ncompeting change to avoid a duplicate. Flagging only in case this session has stalled;\nif so I can carry the confirmed fix to Gerrit."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784233655276896001,"uuid":"8a51fc20-c3f1-4d35-a001-15e85bbf3f1c"}